            . I am an officer. I was walking down Mile-end-road, and saw the prisoner running across the field with a bundle - I pursued, and took him near Stepney church - he said he had met his own mother in Whitechapel-road, and she gave him the bundle.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence, (written). I was persuaded by 
               <persName id="t18260406-262-person1427">
                  Charles 
                  Gigg
               <interp inst="t18260406-262-person1427" type="surname" value="Gigg"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-262-person1427" type="given" value="Charles"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-262-person1427" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , a neighbour, to go to a bull-hunt - as we were in the road, he said "There is a boy with a bundle, we will frighten him" - he told me to send him for two skeins of silk and hold his bundle the while - and when I had it, Gigg ran away and told me to follow - I became alarmed, and asked him to take the bundle - but he said two men were following us.</p>
